Amanda Walker (amanda@intercon.com) writes:

> Or don't use certificates at all and run into the PGP problem.  TANSTAAFL.

*What* PGP problem??? PGP's "web of trust" is just a superset of the
certification hierarchy imposed by RSADSI. If you insist to have a
certification hierarchy, you could just decide to think that Phil
Zimmermann has the "master" key and can other certification nodes.

Therefore, you can (technically) emulate PEM's PCAs with PGP. Now, can 
you tell me how a decentralized web of trust can be handled with PEM?

Regards,
Vesselin
